 all about the same level?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Well they are about the same level I suppose, 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} people are. All inter - married and all that you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Was this true when you were a boy, was everybody about the same then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 No, no, years and years ago - nobody was hardly allowed to come in to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} to live. They wouldn't have 'em in Portland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 What happened then if strangers moved in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Well I suppose different people managed to get in sometimes or other you see, and they started educating them a bit. And they was all right you see. But there's more money in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}
Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} than - anywhere else I reckon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 When you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
No, no. About this - forty-four - forty - forty-six years ago we was living in the other house there, and - the woman that lived next door to us, her father just died. Well when she came back after the funeral sh
e come and shouted over our wall, she said, have you seen anything like this Mr Osborne for a long time? I said, no, oh I said, what is it Mrs Mitchell? So she held her apron out and it was full of sovereigns and half sovereigns. Yes. I said, where did yo
u get all that? Oh, she said, we found a bucketful in - in our old man's cellar what he kept. That was true, yes, Mrs Mitchell wasn't it. Sovereigns and half -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 What did her old man do then?
