\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Were there any people who employed other people to work for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
No, wouldn't employ anybody - any stranger - not in a quarry. Must be Portlanders. Handed down from time and time wasn't it. No when they were in the 
quarry wouldn't. And if you mentioned a single word about those rabbit things oh there'd be murder. Start an argument or fight in a public house or a hotel then start talking about this, they didn't drink up, you didn't do that in front of Portland people
 - they'd throw their jugs at you. I don't know why. Superstitious you see it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Do you ever remember this happening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Somebody really getting that upset?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Yes, well they reckoned the long eared things you see - why they - wouldn'
t speak about those things, they reckoned they used to borrow then under the quarries like that, and - quarry fell down and killed somebody wasn't it, something like that. So the old people says, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did you have much to do with the quarrying people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Who, me? No, no, I wasn't talk to 'em. No. I don't work for no quarries, I wouldn't - I wouldn't work hard like that. Not when you get an easy job for nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did you mix with the quarry people, go out drinking with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 No, I hardly mixed with anybody anyway in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. I was one on my own. He - he was his own master wasn't he. Never go out again you know, well I wasn't allowed to. And for thirty-four years I walked up and down that incline to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 There were the quarrymen and their families, who else would there be on 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} when you were a young man? Was there farmers down the other end of the island?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Well - at - when the - quarries was working here, they brought a lot of people what they called the navies. And in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Grove Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 well there was a field there, they used to put huts in that meadow for 'em to live down there. What they called the navvies that come working for the quarries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 These were not Portlanders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 No, these was - they weren't Portlanders. No - huts down there by - 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} football field that's where they had their huts.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Where did they come from then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Oh anywhere they come from.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did they have their families with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Oh yes, families and wives and all were living down there in the huts.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 What were they building then, the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Quarrying down here for the - stone going down to make the breakwater.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Who were employing those then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 And that big arena place down there - that's - where they were di
gging out weren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 How old were you then, was this between the wars or when you were a young man?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Oh this is before the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Before the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Before the first world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Who was employing them then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Well \{BLANK\}
 Two or three different firms you see come here - quarrying and one thing and another and brought all the navvies with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Was this when the first company from outside came and brought up the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} quarries?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Yes. And then those navvies 
used to come in and do it you see. Well not long ago there was - one of the old lady's used to live across here, Mrs Bosham, she was from the navvy people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Was there trouble between the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} people and the navvies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 No, they never used to mix
 up you see, well - living across the road and people used to live in there. Jack Huckle and - Joseph Bond and all that lot. I know all their names and all that you see. Huckle, Bond - oh - Huckson. Stone.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did the navvies mix on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} or not or did the Portlanders shun them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
No they didn't shun 'em, they used to meet in the public house you see that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 And in the shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Well I wasn't born - I wasn't born then. Soldiers were sent out once you know when there was a riot here once, when the Portlander people and people wanted to come in. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 When was this then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Well - the Verne soldiers turned out. That was a riot you know, oh yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 You were only a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Mm. Oh no, I could have been thirteen - no, not a chi
ld, I was getting on in age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 What happened exactly do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
No I don't know, there was a - threw out, the navvies got on all right afterwards you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Was it through the navvies arriving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Yes. When the navvies arrived or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 What did the Portlanders do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Oh they carried up there with them there shovels and goodness knows what. Going to murder Dick, Tom and Harry. They didn't half go on. Mm. Oh yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Were there still farmers down the end of the island when you were a boy?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Farmers? Yes, we used to have a flock of sheep here. Oh I suppose about - nearly a thousand sheep. You could drive 'em down Portland Fortuneswell and take 'em down - Castletown there and dip 'em in the salt water. Yes. Oh yes, an
d that same man as bring the coal, his grandfather was the old shepherd. We had some - great fun as children, very nice here, we always - I always got on all right with 'em. Never used to have no trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Then you've got the convicts and the staff of - along here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Yes \{BLANK\} up here
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} people mix with the prison staff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Oh no, they was all on their own. Quarry - prison staff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 What did the Portlanders think of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 'Cos - no, they never used to take any notice of 'em. Mm. \{BLANK\}
 Can't sort of live in this block, this house then they were in next door. They never used to mix many in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 at all. Because when I used to come off duty, before I was married, used to cycle off out in the country miles and miles. Yes. Yes. Yes, man by the name of Tom Baker. We used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15539639\charrsid2572417 pack up}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417  on the Friday, shove off and come back Sunday night. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Where did you stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Well we just made a - trip. Go - going to a relative somewhere you see, go down to Stoke Abbott or go 
down to Ber Regis and different places like that. Well I know a friend of mine with cycling going down to Ber Regis one weekend, and it started thundering and lightening like blazes and we only had bikes you see. But we got the bikes stuck in the hedge th
e
re, and we got nearly drowned. But we never had any destination where we was making for. The old girl says, good gracious alive, you must be wet through. I said, wet through, I said, I'm shivering. The lady was going to change all our clothes and dry us o
ff before we could - sit down. That was hectic time wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 A bike was something in those days because it cost a lot of money didn't it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Yes. And another time Tom Baker and I were cycling away, where - I don't know where we was going along - w
e was going a long way away. And - we went into a public house in a village and there was some old witch in there, some old woman, a Gippo lady she was, she says, where are you going you two? Oh we're going to - she said, you won't get there. You won't ge
t
 there tonight. And old Tom Baker said to me he said, here come on you let's get out of this. I said, well, I said, don't stop and talk to that silly old bitch there, I said, get on out. So as we was coming out she said, you won't drink this? I looked rou
n
d, I said, I don't know how to stand with you. Anyhow we jumped on the bikes - started going on - I suppose we got about three and a half miles from this place when his free wheel went. He was going - I was going right down the bottom of the hill you know
 
and a man coming down on a motor bike says, here, your mate's up - there, he says, carry - come - coming down. Oh I turned round and held up. What's up Tom? Oh he said, the wheel. Free wheel was gone. I said, well, I said, we'll push it back in now, I sai
d
, and go with that blasted old woman in - I suppose it's the only thing we can do. Push the bikes up, we were coming down, she was still there. She said, haven't got there then have you? Oh I used to swear then something terrible. I said, no, I said, we h
a
ven't got there. So I said to the landlord I said - I suppose you don't know whether anybody's got a bicycle shop down here? Well, he said, there's one just on the corner over there. I said to Tom, I said, here, I'm going to take this over and get a new f
r
ee wheel. I pushed his bike up to there and rode me own, I said to the bloke I said, here, can you make - fix up a free wheel on this bike? Oh, he said, I expect as I could, but it won't be today. Oh, I said, my God, well when can we have it? Well I'll te
l
l you what I'll do, he said, where are you going? I told him where we were going. Well I'll lend you one of my bicycles, when you're coming back this way again - come in and you can have your own bike. So I said to old Tom, right-o Tom, I said, we'll try 
a
gain. So this bike you see this bloke lent me - come on out, started going out, that woman said - you - you going to have another try? Yes, I said, come on. Started off again. Oh I suppose we got about six miles away - then the blasted tyre broke right th
e
re, the wire in them - with in struts you see, they was going all on like that and the tyre burst - busted. I said to Tom, I said, if I had my way, I said, I'd throw these bikes in the hedge, I said, and - lay down and stop here. Oh what a hectic time. Sh
e was right. We wasn't going to get there that night. So I said to Tom I said, well, I said, come on lets - well turn round and make our way back to Dorset as soon as we can. When we started to come home there on the Sunday night do you know the way? \{
BLANK\} Unintelligible. \{BLANK\} I said to Tom I said, I'm not going that way again, I said, bugger all to see out here. A hectic time that was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 How far did you get on these trips then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Oh a bit; miles and miles we used to go. Travelling - well travel
ing all night sometimes. Used to be of a Friday night when we used to pack up on Friday night. And Saturday morning you see when we used to get to a destination. Just about ten o'clock because they was open all day then. Oh we had some hectic times though
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 So your entertainments then were cycling and recovering afterwards in the sun?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Yes. We used to - used to cycle then miles and miles and miles. Once we was coming back from a trip and old Tom says, old Tom says well he says, let's go down to Dor
chester tonight. I says, well all right, I says - go on, I don't mind. Well we put the bikes up, I reckon - got so me \{BLANK\}
 So he says to me, he says, well just go up in the field and sit down. I said, right-o. We're going up on the field and sit down but all the - \{BLANK\}
 start walking all round us you know, and the farmers. Yes. I said, oh Tom, I said, here, want to - let's get out of this quick. Oh God. Used to have a hectic time over there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 What about shopkeepers on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Shopkeepers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Were there a lot of shopkeepers, were they all small shops or were there any bigger ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Oh no, they were their own property weren't they, all the shops and that. Yes, there was old Hillier, he had a shop. And there was a man by the name of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Austin{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}, he had a shop. Newmans had a shop. They all - all their own property you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Did these people consider themselves the same as the quarrymen or did they or did they think of themselves as better?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Well, no you used to get different people in those days than was now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 How about the clergyman then, was he thought of as being at all different?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Well one clergyman, yes, he wasn't bad, one clergyman. Reverend Gregg, a nice man. He wrote to me when I was abroad you know. And when I came ba
ck home - wife said to me, you ought to go to church you know, I said, right-o. So he happened to spot me - walk through the church you see, and he brought up in the church it was - something - boys - just come back home. Very few of us comeback you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Were you brought up to call anybody master or sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Was I brought up to bring - call anybody master? No. No, I was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did you touch your cap to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 I would - no, I wouldn't life me that off to nobody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Was there anybody you had to show respect to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Oh yes, they used to go out and inspect us you know. Collar and tie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Was there anybody you had to respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Were there any real ladies or real gentlemen on the island?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Oh yes, there was. Oh one or two, the
re was - Farmer Comber, Dan Hodder. And all - all the big family Laro's. All people like that you see, they had farms and goodness knows what here. Farmer Comber he had a big farm. Dan White, Jack White, they were the two butchers. 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Austin{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, he had a big shop up there you know, Newman had a shop here. Co-op had a big shop down {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Easton{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} then, it wasn't Co-op then it was - what was the name of that big fat woman? And then - then they all had their own shops. There was Morris, he had a butchers shop. There was Pie
r had that big fish shop. Bill Pearce had a bakers shop. Dunkley had a bakers shop. Then Reid had a barbers shop.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Would you say your family was the same level as all these families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 I suppose so, they used to look after one another. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 W
as there any difference between the standards of living in different families on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 No, no. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Were there any particularly poor families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
There wasn't - there wasn't the money about in them days not some of the poor people you see. Gaffer Sanson owned that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did you ever mix with him at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did I mix with him? Oh I met - I met Gaffer Sanson
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
How did you treat Gaffer Sanson them, did you talk to him the same as anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Oh yes, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Even when you were quite young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Even when I was quite young I used to \{BLANK\}
 That's true. No that never used to worry me, I never used to take any notice of him you see. In fact if I wanted to go away from the island I used to pack up - get the first train and off somewhere. They had a special trip going up to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 once. It was only cost - five bob you see for the day, leaving here about five o'clock in the morning and leaving about four o'clock the next morning to come back. Well I went up with 'e
m, this trip. I waited up there on the platform then, I said, I hope I get a train. They said, come on Harry, come on, you won't get home yet. I ain't going. I stopped another week. All on me own. Yes, they went and I was going to stop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 How old were you then then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Oh about twenty. That's all isn't it. Twenty-four I had the key.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 You say they were some people who were very poor on the island?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Well some of 'em were, yes, well - you weren't brought up like that any other way you see. Some
 of 'em are poor, they - but they used to make - ends meet every time you know. Never seen any of 'em starve, did you? No they weren't the wages they had in those days. Very poor. Oh yes, plenty of money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 What would happen when someone was out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 When }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15539639\charrsid2572417 someone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417  was out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 What would happen to the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Was never any out of work here. Oh you had the quarry working then you see, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 You said your father was out of work quite a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Oh yes, he was out of wor
k because he was too tired to work you see. I used to work for him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 But what happened when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
When I was little? Yes. Well I - I don't know what - that's going a long way back because there's so much in my brain up here - I think about this and think about that. I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
What would happen to a family with small children if the father couldn't work, if he had an accident or he didn't work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Oh there's no - there was never many poor people about, not what you call very 
poor. They always used to make ends meet somehow, even if they just had a bit of bread and butter or bread and marg or something like that. To make their meals on that, they never used to bother. See used to make a lot of this here bread pudding. And what
 they call toad in the hole, that sausage stuff up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 What would you have in the morning for breakfast when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Well I used to have a lot of that - porridge, that - what was that stuff? No, no, no. That's a long time ago. I forget now. Weetabix, no, no. It was like little biscuits. What is the name of it. I know I got somebody to get some for me the other day.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Was it a sort of a cereal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Yes. Used to have plenty of pot - plenty of veg and all that in those days. Potatoes, cabbage, parsnips or anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Where did they all come from then when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Where did they come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did your mother buy vegetables or did your father grow them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Oh we used to buy it all. Buy it all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 What w
ould you have at dinnertime then when you were at school, when you used to come home from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
I used to have a lump of bread and marg and go outside and eat it. You know what they're like when they're young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Would you have a cooked meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Oh yes, Sunday, always had a cooked meal of a Sunday. Cooked dinner Sunday and all roast potatoes, any other time they come home from school if there was no - meat, bacon and all that we used to have for dinner, bacon, potatoes, boiled potatoes. But we 
never had mashed potatoes and stuff like this. Most baked potatoes and things like that. Well I expect then they never had the stuff in the house then to cook nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Was there always plenty of food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Always plenty of food, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Could you always have what you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Oh always, yes, get - full up you see and then going back to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Do you ever remember there not being enough for you all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Yes, used to be enough, yes, for the lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Do you ever remember your mother sort of not having very much to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
No, me mother got on whether she had food or not in those days. Mum and dad used to get - used to eat more sweets than anything else. Licorice allsorts and different stuffs like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Where did you get those from?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Pennyworth a pound, penny - what they call - now what - lucky penny. Penny go in and get one of these little bags, you'd get one or two little bits and pieces in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Where did you get your penny from, did you earn it or was it pocket money?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Oh I used to - run errands for anybody else and if they had a bit of money they'd give us a copper or two. Like Mrs - what was her name, Mrs Gibbs. Down - down Artist Row. I always used to go and get her glass of beer you see, and she always 
used to give me a big lump of cake like that for getting it. There was another woman stood outside the door saying - seventeen pounds a night my boy, seventeen pounds a night. Then I should go and get her seventeen pints a night you see. I can't remember 
now, what was her name? Mrs Gibbs I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did you have pocket money at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
No, I only used to have pocket money - you see, if there were three of us - had to earn some you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 What were mealtimes like in your family when you were a boy at 
home, did you have to sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Underneath. Yes, had to sit round the table, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did you have to behave yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Oh yes, oh Lord, yes. When the old man was sitting down he used to say, you shut up. Tell the old man to shut up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Were you allowed to talk or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
No, weren't allowed to speak over the table. I was the only one used to say me prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did you have a special place at the table you had to sit at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Yes, mine was on the corner, always on the corner. 
So I could get out first. Quite right I used to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Were you allowed to choose what you wanted to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
No, it was put on the table you've got to eat it. Oh no, you couldn't pick or choose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did you have to eat it all up? Or could you leave anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 No, we wasn't to leave anything. Eat it all up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
If you wanted something like the salt or something that was on the table were you allowed to speak to ask for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Oh no, no, you ; wait you see like you see with our first course 
and if there was anything else to come - just put it on the plate, say, get on with that now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 If there was enough left. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did you have to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Yes. I used to use my fork upside down, have the other end in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 What did your mother say about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Oh no, never used to. Never used to tell you nothing, always a devil I was, I didn't care.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Could you get down from the table when you finished or did you h
ave to stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Oh no, when you finished you got up for going back to school you see then in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did anybody have to wait though until the meal was finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Oh wait until the meal was finished before you leave the table. Oh yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Everybody got down together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 That's right, yes, or you'd get something thrown at you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Do you remember having to feed the young children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Did I feed the other children? Oh yes, used to have some of mine. Always wanted some of my food. Say, here you are, get on with it, eat it and I'll go without. But I could always get plenty of food 'cos I used to go out working for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 How did you work for it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Well - go and see me old grandmother and Aunt Bess and all down her
e you see. Got to go in places you see - if you can get something to eat, then going in next door get something there. Oh I was never hungry. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did you go and do this because you were hungry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 No, I don't think I was ever hungry. I'm afraid if
 I went hungry like that I should have gone and - begged for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
Did your mother feed the little ones or was it the job of the older ones to feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
No, mother used to feed 'em you see the young ones. I couldn't go sticking dummies in their mouths and one thing and another like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did your family keep any hens or pigs or anything any livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Only - only the human pigs. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Your father didn't grow any vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 No, well I used to keep myself a - those tame wilfreds
, pigeons, chickens and all that I used to keep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Was this when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Before I was married this was. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 How old were you then when you started doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Oh about fifteen I suppose. That's going back a few years isn't it? Fifteen.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did you keep them on your own then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Did your father know anything about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
No, he wouldn't - he - he would never kill a pig. Wouldn't kill a bird let alone anything else would he? No, he was one of those - lah-
di-dahs. Lah-di-dahs. I've got a photo there - I had a photo somewhere of the four sons serving with him. What have I done with that, do you know? Well I never see her no more. Yes. No, I never saw her no more. Then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 What happened when you were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 
When I was in? Never knowed in my life. And it's the truth. This is my father's photograph. There you see. Look at his photo. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15539639\charrsid2572417 Here look}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 , that's him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15539639\charrsid2572417 He looks}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417  smart, is he in his Army uniform?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 That was the Army, the first world war. Oh that's
 all my French friends. That's all my French friends that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Who did you play football for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Portland
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 How old were you when you started playing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Oh before the war that was, before the first world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3373851 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 When did you play, Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11492710 HO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2583594\charrsid2572417 Yes. Yes, on the Saturday at corner.
